      • createCreditCard

        public void createCreditCard(@NonNull
                             CreditCardInfo creditCardInfo,
                             @NonNull
                             ApiCallback<CreditCard> callback)
        Add a single credit card to a user's profile. If the card owner has no default card, then the new card will become the default. However, if the owner already has a default then it will not change. To change the default, you should update the user to have a new "default_source".

        Important note: This call responds with a hypermedia link for accept terms. Getting the card again will not result in the proper hypermedia link. It's your own responsibility to store CreditCard.getAcceptTermsUrl() and restore CreditCard.setAcceptTermsUrl(String) this link allowing the user to come back to the T&Cs at a later time

        Parameters:
        creditCardInfo - credit card data:(pan, expMonth, expYear, cvv, name, address data:(street1, street2, street3, city, state, postalCode, country))
        callback - result callback

      • createCreditCard

        public void createCreditCard(@NonNull
                             CreditCardInfo creditCardInfo,
                             @NonNull
                             java.lang.String deviceId,
                             @NonNull
                             ApiCallback<CreditCard> callback)
        Add a single credit card to a user's profile. If the card owner has no default card, then the new card will become the default. However, if the owner already has a default then it will not change. To change the default, you should update the user to have a new "default_source".

        Important note: This call responds with a hypermedia link for accept terms. Getting the card again will not result in the proper hypermedia link. It's your own responsibility to store CreditCard.getAcceptTermsUrl() and restore CreditCard.setAcceptTermsUrl(String) this link allowing the user to come back to the T&Cs at a later time

        Parameters:
        creditCardInfo - credit card data:(pan, expMonth, expYear, cvv, name, address data:(street1, street2, street3, city, state, postalCode, country))
        deviceId - id of the device the credit card should create a credential for
        callback - result callback
